OL,3,CTata Steel's timeline for greener
OL,4,Csteelmaking in Port Talbot
OL,6,FTraditional iron and steelmaking has
OL,7,Fcome to an end in Port Talbot, with
OL,8,Fthe closure of the heavy end assets
OL,9,Fincluding the final blast furnace, the
OL,10,Fsinter plant and the steel plant.
OL,12,FTata Steel who operate the
OL,13,Fsteelworkers confirmed the final tap
OL,14,Fof molten material was made on Blast
OL,15,FFurnace 4 on Monday 30 September.
OL,17,FBosses at the Indian steel company
OL,18,Finsist it is only a matter of time
OL,19,Funtil a new, greener operation is
OL,20,Funderway.
