OL,3,CTata Steel's timeline for greener
OL,4,Csteelmaking in Port Talbot
OL,6,FElectric currents are passed through
OL,7,Fthe electrodes which heat up the
OL,8,Ffurnace like an oven and melts the
OL,9,Fscrap steel.
OL,11,FLimestone, fluorspar, carbon and
OL,12,Foxygen can then be added to purify the
OL,13,Fsteel.
OL,15,FThe arc furnace uses a lot less energy
OL,16,Fthan blast furnaces and are said to be
OL,17,F"greener". If 100% of the material
OL,18,Fused is scrap metal, scientists
OL,19,Fsuggests that only 0.67 tonnes of CO2
OL,20,Fis produced per tonne of steel.
